node.text:
The glorious Cotswold hotel @thyme.england was founded with an ethos of caring for and celebrating the land, an ethos expressed through its beautiful gardens, botanically inspired decoration, and seasonal cooking based around locally grown (often home-grown) produce. This summer (starting June 15) Thyme is staging its first exhibition in the estate's restored Tithe Barn – a celebration of the country meadow in pressed flowers by Brixton-based @jamjar_flowers. In time for the launch of the exhibition on June 15, the JamJar team have created a charming tutorial on how to press flowers especially for House & Garden.

Film by @frederickjewson
Thanks to @long_elgar

node.title: How to press flowers with JamJar and Thyme

node.text: March is the month when seed sowing starts in earnest, and our own @clarefostergardens has been preparing hers in her garden in Berkshire. In this video from her greenhouse, she talks us through how to sow seeds, discussing the the vegetables she's sowing, like chard and beetroot, and flowers like calendula and phlox.

node.title: How to sow seeds with our garden editor Clare Foster

node.text: House & Garden’s creative director of interiors Gabby Deeming shows how she would use her favourite pieces from the Fall 2020 @ralphlaurenhome collection, in the scheme for an imaginary London apartment. ‘In my head I suppose the space is a rather lovely first floor London apartment, with nice tall ceilings and panelled walls. It feels elegant and spacious. Lots of room for those big scale Ralph Lauren Home pieces.’

node.title: Ralph Lauren Home’s new collection styled by House & Garden

node.text: 'I Can't Breathe' a piece of choreography by Principal of the Royal Ballet @marcisambe created in memory of George Floyd who was murdered in Minnesota last week. Expect more from us over the coming weeks. For now we urge you to support @blklivesmatter and @blmuk, and keep the conversation about how we can change going forward.

node.text:
Just in time for Easter, florist and stylist @willowcrossleycreates shows us how to set a stylish Easter table using flowers grown in her garden and pieces of @gpjbaker fabric from her stores.
Directed by @luca_lamaro

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by House & Garden Magazine in London, United Kingdom. May be an image of sofa and living room.

node.text:
Charged with adding character to a London flat modernised by a property developer, @max_rollitt has used his antiques expertise and taken inspiration from the flat's former appearance to create interiors with a feeling of permanence in a Victorian hospital building. Sixteenth-century style panelling gives the sitting room an early English vernacular flavour. Follow the link in our profile to read the full story.
📸 @simonbrownphotography

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by House & Garden Magazine in Dominican Republic. May be an image of furniture and living room.

node.text:
@playagrandebeachclub is a charming hotel on the north coast of the Dominican Republic offering the best of the country's azure water and tropical jungle in a remote setting far off the beaten track. Every room in all of the nine residences and public areas is different, and each is painted in what the owner and designer @celerie calls, 'faded bathing-suit colours', and layered with art, objects and vintage furnishings. Follow the link in our profile to see the rest of the interiors.
📸 @minh_ngoc

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by House & Garden Magazine in Bray, Berkshire. May be an image of furniture and living room.

node.text:
The dealer and designer Christopher Howe of @howelondon had initially advised the owner of this house in Bray against using an interior designer. ‘I told him not to bother. He has a great eye...' But things snowballed, ‘the odd phone call’ became a site visit and, before long, Christopher was overseeing all of the decoration. As with all his projects, attention to detail is the mainspring: the walls of the snug are panelled and tacked with steel pins in a linen and horsehair fabric, which was once used for interlining suits. Follow the link in our profile to read the full story.
📸 @lucasallenphoto

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by House & Garden Magazine in Connecticut. May be an image of table and living room.

node.text:
‘We have always wanted an old house, but also loved the fact that it had grown over time and been added on to,’ says the owner of this 18th-century farmhouse in Connecticut. Seeking a restful retreat from Manhattan life, they called in interior designer @fordhuniford to update the house, avoiding anything too fussy or formal. In the dining area, the walls are lined with old French grain sacks, creating the backdrop for a Dutch chandelier by H Berlage. Follow the link in our profile to read the full story.
📸@minh_ngoc

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by House & Garden Magazine in Hampshire. May be an image of 1 person and indoor.

node.text:
On the site of a former vicarage in Hampshire, Andrew and Sarah Hills of @portaromanauk have created an elegant and distinguished family house, which has an established feel despite its modern reconstruction. The moods of the rooms are diverse, moving from cool and refined in the living room to opulent and colourful in the dining room, then to ultra modern in the kitchen, and pretty and traditional in the main bedroom. @farrowandball's ‘Black Blue’ paint adds to the dark, moody atmosphere in this library corner.
📸 @michaelsinclair | @houseandgardenuk

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by House & Garden Magazine in Montalcino. May be an image of tree and outdoors.

node.text:
In the picturesque surroundings of the Tuscan hills, @camillaguinness' elegant eighteenth-century farmhouse Arniano is a heavenly retreat from the world outside. Home to @arnianopaintingschool, run by Camilla's daughter @amberguinness, the house is imbued with a sense of the good life: nurturing meals, creativity, convivial interiors and a close relationship with nature. Camilla designed much of the Arniano garden furniture, including these bespoke day beds dressed in bold red and white stripes. Follow the link in our profile to read the full story, an extract from Robyn Lea's new book 'A Room of Her Own', published by @thamesandhudsonau.
📸@robynleaphotography

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by House & Garden Magazine in Wiltshire. May be an image of indoor.

node.text:
Outdoor-antique experts Travers and Katie Nettleton of @gardenartplus are the owners of this house in Wiltshire's Savernake Forest. The two of them united and modernised the cottages – the oldest parts of which date back to the 17th century – and added to them as their family grew, as well as fashioning a glorious garden on the edge of the forest, with an unblemished vista of Wiltshire fields and hedgerows. In the snug, in the oldest part of the house, a Bridget Riley artwork hangs above an old settle from India. Follow the link in our profile to read the full story.
📸@dean.hearne

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by House & Garden Magazine in Maine with @mauramcevoy, @basha_oog, @kathleenhackett, @vendomepress, @themainehouse_thebook, @thefieldlighting, and @ohpottery. May be an image of indoor.

node.text:
Photographer and lighting designer Chris Baker (@thefieldlighting) and his wife, Odette Heideman (@ohpottery), a literary editor and ceramicist, fell for this 1850s Cape house while visiting Maine several years ago. The pair have decorated the various buildings on the property (a big house, a little house, a back house and a barn) using natural materials from the surrounding area. The barn doubles as guest quarters and a breezy space for summer dinner parties. The house is featured in a new book from @vendomepress, 'The Maine House'. Follow the link in our profile to see the full story.
📸@mauramcevoy

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by House & Garden Magazine in The Bahamas. May be an image of sofa and living room.

node.text:
When a story begins with 'we'd been invited for drinks on Valentino's yacht one summer...', one might reasonably expect to be regaled with tales of glamour and of decadence, but the interior designer John McCall, who decorated this house in the Bahamas, was mainly interested in the combinations of colours and materials on the fashion designer's boat. He was determined to use the same ideas one day, and when he got the brief for this house – that it shouldn't be 'too beachy' - he knew he'd found the right place. In the library, the cypress-panelled walls are decorated with maps of the Caribbean. The pattern on the blinds matches the one on the rug. Follow the link in our profile to read the full story. 
📸@alexanderjamesphoto

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by House & Garden Magazine in North Rode. May be an image of flower, nature and tree.

node.text:
North Rode Manor in Cheshire is a place that rarely goes for long without rain, but for the garden designer @chrismoss.garden – who was brought up in Lancashire – the lushness of the countryside was a huge draw. Rectangles of box and uprights of yew, or pleached hornbeam – as well as the ever-expanding woodland – are the garden’s main feature, and here the flower garden planted mostly with texture and pale colours in mind. Follow the link in our profile to read the full story.
📸 @eva_nemeth

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by House & Garden Magazine in Somerset. May be an image of nature, the Cotswolds and tree.

node.text:
@farrowandball’s colour curator @joastudholme has applied her talents to her own 19th-century schoolhouse in rural Somerset, using carefully chosen hues in each room. The exterior of the house and its hillside setting is just as beautiful, with a Hadspen stone structure and a garden that looks out over the Somerset countryside. Follow the link in our profile to read the full story.
📸 @andreasvoneinsiedel

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by House & Garden Magazine in Dorset. May be an image of living room.

node.text:
‘It’s my version of a crisp, fresh take on country-house style,’ says @samanthatodhunterdesign, explaining the aesthetic she brought to this 16th-century farmhouse in Dorset. With views over the Stour Valley and plenty of charm in its bones, it was a dream project for Samantha to take on, helped by her harmonious working relationship with her clients. In the hall, chairs from Paolo Moschino for @nicholashaslamltd are paired with a ‘Scroll Bracket Console’ table and wall lights from @soanebritain. Follow the link in our profile to read the full story.
📸 @simonbrownphotography

Samantha Todhunter is a member of @thelistbyhouseandgarden
